On 18-Apr-08, at 4:43 PM, George Lyle wrote:

> Swapping the
> rear hubs. brakes. etc. would fix that.

you have to be careful here because the compound drum setup of the 71- 
up buses is wider than the 68-70, which is why the later buses have  
the flared rear wheel opening. the tires might rub if you put the  
late drums on a early bus.


